column3: Agujam is worried by what lurks beneath the sands.
Slay any diremites that appear in the rocky area to the west.
Do these foul creatures not rest!?
Ah, you there, adventurer. Should you be willing, I would like your help with something.

I have sighted an unusually large number of diremites in the area of late. They always appear after sandstorms. This would not be a problem if they fought fairly. However, they choose to cower beneath the sands, waiting to strike when you are vulnerable.
Slay any that you find by the rocky area to the west and I shall see you are rewarded suitably. You have my word.
Slay any that you find by the rocky area to the west and I shall see you are rewarded suitably. You have my word.
The beasts have been slain? You have my thanks.
If the diremites only attacked warriors such as ourselves, this would not have been such a problem. But they will prey on anyone. Women, children, it matters not to them.
I will not stand for this. We must not rest until they have been eradicated from the area.
Thank you for helping me to dispatch the first few of them. We will take care of the rest.
